<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
    <title>Price and weight encoding</title>
    <meta content="Dave Proffitt" name="author">
    <link href="css/style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="header"> <img id="logo" src="Logo.gif" alt="ProffittCenter logo"
        title="ProffittCenter logo" style="width: 124px; height: 124px;"
        checked="true">Price and weight encoding</div>
    <p class="rvps3"><span class="rvts10">There is not a universal
        standard for price encoded barcodes but it is hoped that what
        has been implemented will be suitable for most applications.
        When creating a new product with the </span><a class="rvts16" href="Newproduct.html">New

        product</a><span class="rvts10"> screen, if the barcode could </span><span
        class="rvts10">be a price encoded barcode, there is an drop down
        box enabled, labelled Encoded that one can select one of three
        options:</span></p>
    <ul style="text-indent: 0px; margin-left: 13px; list-style-position: outside;">
      <li class="rvps7" style="margin-left: 0; text-indent: 0px"><span class="rvts10">Normal</span></li>
      <li class="rvps7" style="margin-left: 0; text-indent: 0px"><span class="rvts10">Price

          encoded</span></li>
      <li class="rvps7" style="margin-left: 0; text-indent: 0px"><span class="rvts10">Weight

          encoded.</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="rvps3"><span class="rvts10">Choose the correct setting and
        in the case of </span><a class="rvts16" href="Encodedproducts.html">Weight

        encoded</a><span class="rvts10">, enter the price per kg in the
        price box. For </span><a class="rvts16" href="Encodedproducts.html">Price

        encoded</a><span class="rvts10">, the price will be set to 0.</span></p>
    <p class="rvps3"><span class="rvts10">When the product is
        subsequently scanned, the correct price will be shown.</span></p>
    <p class="rvps3"><span class="rvts10"></span></p>
    <p class="rvps3"><span class="rvts10"></span></p>
    <p></p>
  </body>
</html>
